SIMPLE: ingrain
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingrain
<hw>In"grain`</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>grain</ets> kermes. See <er>Engrain</er>,
<er>Grain</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Dyed with grain, or kermes.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dyed before manufacture, -- said of the material of
a textile fabric; hence, in general, thoroughly inwrought; forming an
essential part of the substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ingrain carpet</b></col>, <cd>a double or two-ply
carpet.</cd> -- <col><b>Triple ingrain carpet</b></col>, <cd>a three-ply
carpet.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingrain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ingrain
<hw>In"grain`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An ingrain fabric, as a
carpet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingrain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ingrain
<hw>In"grain`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Ingrained</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Ingraining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Written also
<ets>engrain</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To dye with or in grain or kermes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dye in the grain, or before
manufacture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To work into the natural texture or into the mental
or moral constitution of; to stain; to saturate; to imbue; to infix
deeply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our fields <qex>ingrained</qex> with blood.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cruelty and jealousy seem to be <qex>ingrained</qex> in a man who
has these vices at all.</q> <rj><qau>Helps.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ingraining</ent>⟦br⟧
